# TypeScript Standards

- Strict mode; no `any`
- Typed props, events, API responses
- Prefer `type` for object shapes; `interface` for extendable contracts
- Valid HTML attributes; avoid invalid props

```typescript
// Good: Typed props
type ButtonProps = {
  label: string;
  onClick: () => void;
  disabled?: boolean;
};

// Good: Typed API response
type SubmitResult = { success: boolean; message?: string };

// Bad: any
function handle(data: any) {} // Avoid
```
